A nurse who works at the Charlotte Maxeke Academic Hospital in Johannesburg has described her calm in the midst of a storm the day the facility caught fire. The blaze could only be extinguished after 24 hours. eNCA's Masego Rahlaga spoke to her. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A nurse who works at the Charlotte Maxeke Academic Hospital in Johannesburg has described her calm in the midst of a storm the day the facility caught fire. The hospital was shut down last week after a fire damaged some parts of the building. READ: Charlotte Maxeke Hospital to reopen in May More than 800 patients had to be moved to other facilities. The hospital is expected to resume some services next week. eNCA's Masego Rahlaga spoke to the nurse on condition of anonymity.